description:
In lora_l2.c:149-150, lora_recv() returns the number of bytes received, which is used directly as the length parameter to the RX callback:

ret = lora_recv(lora_state.lora_dev, rx_buf, sizeof(rx_buf), ...);
...
cb(rx_buf, ret, rssi, snr, cb_user_data);  // line 173

Location: firmware/bridge-zephyr/subsys/lichen/lora_l2.c:149-173

The code checks ret < 0 (error) and ret == 0 (empty), but does not validate that ret <= sizeof(rx_buf). If the Zephyr LoRa driver misbehaves and returns a length exceeding the buffer size, the callback receives an incorrect length that could cause out-of-bounds access in downstream handlers.

Impact: Out-of-bounds read if Zephyr LoRa driver returns invalid length. Defense-in-depth issue - requires driver bug.

Fix: Add check after ret > 0:
if ((size_t)ret > sizeof(rx_buf)) {
    LOG_ERR("LoRa driver returned invalid length: %d > %zu", ret, sizeof(rx_buf));
    continue;
}
